
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant WA as Web Application
    participant CB as Chatbot
    participant A as Agent (Digital Assistant)
    participant LLM as LLM
    participant PID as Ping Identity IDM/IAM
    participant AG as Agent Gateway
    participant PA as Ping Authorize
    participant MCP as MCP
    participant RS as Resource Server (OAuth 2.1)

    Note over A: Agent starts
    A->>PID: Token request (client_credentials, resource: agent-gateway)
    PID-->>A: Access token (sub: banking_agent, aud: agent-gateway)

    Note over A: Request tool list
    A->>AG: tools/list (JSON-RPC) with agent token
    AG->>PA: Authorization check (agent token)
    PA->>PID: Introspect agent token
    PID-->>PA: Token claims (sub, aud, scope)
    PA->>MCP: Get available tools list
    MCP-->>PA: Available tools list
    Note over PA: Fine-grained policy evaluation:<br/>return allowed tools for this agent
    PA-->>AG: Permitted tool list for agent
    AG-->>A: List of available tools

    Note over U: User makes request "Check my balance"
    U->>CB: "Check my balance"
    CB->>A: Invoke check_balance tool
    A->>LLM: Tool list + chatbot prompt
    LLM-->>A: Determine tool to use (check_balance)

    Note over A: Tool call — agent context only <br/> (no user subject token)
    A->>AG: tools/call check_balance (JSON-RPC)
    AG->>PA: Authorization check
    PA-->>AG: Deny (insufficient_scope: balance, no subject token)
    AG-->>A: JSON-RPC error (insufficient_scope: balance, no subject token)

    A-->>CB: User context required (resource: banking_agent, scope: balance)

    Note over CB,WA: User already authenticated <br/>Obtain scoped subject token
    Note over CB,WA: If user is not authenticated,<br/>an authn event is triggered first
    CB->>WA: Request token (resource: banking_agent, scope: balance)
    WA->>PID: Token request (resource: banking_agent, scope: balance)
    PID-->>WA: Subject token (sub: user, aud: banking_agent, may_act: {sub: banking_agent}, scope: balance)
    WA-->>CB: Subject token (sub: user, aud: banking_agent, may_act: {sub: banking_agent}, scope: balance)
    CB->>A: Subject token (sub: user, aud: banking_agent, may_act: {sub: banking_agent})

    Note over A,PID: Exchange token for Agent Gateway (RFC 8693)
    A->>PID: Token exchange (actor_token: agent token, subject_token: user token, resource: agent-gateway)
    PID-->>A: TX token (sub: user, act: {sub: banking_agent}, aud: agent-gateway, scope: balance)
    Note over A: sub=user, act=banking_agent — Agent acts on behalf of user
    Note over A: Option: aud: mcp-olb<br/>(requires assurance only path to MCP is via gateway)

    A->>AG: tools/call check_balance (JSON-RPC) with TX token

    Note over AG,PA: Gateway authorizes TX token + tool call
    AG->>PA: Authorization check (TX token, tool: check_balance)
    PA->>PID: Introspect TX token
    PID-->>PA: Token claims (sub, act, aud, scope)
    Note over PA: Validate: aud, scope: balance,<br/>tool call details vs. policy
    Note over PA,PID: Exchange token for MCP
    PA->>PID: Token exchange (TX token → resource: mcp)
    PID-->>PA: MCP token (sub: user, act: {sub: banking_agent}, aud: mcp, scope: balance)
    PA-->>AG: Permit + MCP token
    AG->>MCP: tools/call check_balance (JSON-RPC) with MCP token
    Note over MCP,PID: Exchange token for Resource Server
    MCP->>PID: Token exchange (MCP token → resource: resource-server)
    PID-->>MCP: RS token (sub: user, act: {sub: banking_agent}, aud: resource-server, scope: balance)
    MCP->>RS: GET /balance (RS token)
    RS->>PID: Introspect RS token
    PID-->>RS: Token claims (sub, act, aud, scope)
    Note over RS: Validate: aud=resource-server,<br/>scope: balance, act: banking_agent
    RS-->>MCP: Balance data
    MCP-->>AG: Tool result
    AG-->>A: Tool result
    A->>LLM: Tool result + context
    LLM-->>A: Natural language response
    A-->>CB: Response
    CB-->>U: "Your balance is..."
